<section class="paranoia-dialogue" aria-labelledby="paranoia-orientation-title">
  <h2 id="paranoia-orientation-title">Mandatory Citizen Orientation</h2>

  <dl class="paranoia-dialogue__transcript">
    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">May I be of assistance?</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">Sure. Why don't you tell me how this game works?</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">I'm sorry, citizen. That information is not available at this time.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">What do you mean, it's not available?</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">You are not yet a Troubleshooter. Therefore your security clearance is Infrared. The rules are security clearance Red. You are not cleared to know the rules. At your service.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">Huh? Most games are real eager to teach you the rules.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">Not Paranoia. In Paranoia, you don't know who your friends are. You don't know who your enemies are. You don't know how your equipment works. You don't know the rules. One thing you know: everyone is out to get you. Stay alert! Trust no one! Keep your laser handy! Ignorance and fear; fear and ignorance. Those are our watchwords.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">The back cover copy says something about a computer.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">The Computer is your friend! Trust The Computer. In Paranoia, you play a Troubleshooter in service to The Computer: You are The Computer's trusted agent.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">How did I get to be a Troubleshooter?</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">You turned in a friend for treason. He was executed for betraying The Computer. The Computer rewarded you for your loyalty.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">What is a Troubleshooter supposed to do?</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">Your job is to root out all traitors and execute them. In other words, to find trouble&hellip; and then to shoot it.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">What's a &ldquo;traitor&rdquo;?</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">A traitor is an evil and malevolent human who has betrayed his friend The Computer and seeks to destroy The Computer, humanity, Alpha Complex and life as we know it. Traitors must be unmasked and destroyed. All mutants are traitors. They are genetically imperfect. They have no place in utopia. They must be eliminated. All members of secret societies are traitors. They belong to organizations not officially sanctioned by The Computer. They conspire against The Computer. They must be destroyed.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">By the way, you are a mutant. And a member of a secret society.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">I'm a mutant?</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">That's right. All Troubleshooters would be eager to unmask you as a traitor and execute you. You work with many Troubleshooters. All of them carry powerful weapons.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">Let me get this straight. I'm a traitor. The punishment for treason is death. My job is to hunt down and kill traitors. I work with other people, who have the same orders. All of them want to kill me.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">Not exactly. All of them want to kill traitors. They don't know you're a Commie mutant traitor&hellip; yet.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">And if they find out that I'm a mutant, they'll kill me?</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">They'll try. Of course, if you convict them of treason first, then they will be executed, and you may survive. Of course, false accusations of treason are themselves treason.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">So I want to prove that they're traitors before they can prove that I'm a traitor. And if I don't&hellip; I die.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">Precisely. Watch out! Traitors are everywhere! By the way: dead traitors cannot testify to their own innocence &mdash; or against you. It is best to shoot first and ask questions later. Stay alert! Trust no one! Keep your laser handy!</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">Are you sure this is going to be fun?</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">Certainly, citizen! Of course it will be fun. The Computer says so, and The Computer is your friend. Can you doubt The Computer? Doubting The Computer is treason.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--citizen">Citizen</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--citizen">No! No, certainly not. If The Computer says this will be fun, then this certainly will be fun. Only a Commie mutant traitor could believe otherwise.</dd>

    <dt class="paranoia-dialogue__speaker paranoia-dialogue__speaker--computer">The Computer</dt>
    <dd class="paranoia-dialogue__line paranoia-dialogue__line--computer">Excellent, citizen! You're getting the idea. You have just been promoted to security clearance Red. Welcome to Paranoia.</dd>
  </dl>
</section>
